Client connect to server:
 client->DNS server, domain name resolution to get the ip address of the server.
 client->server, client connects to the server, server allocates an unique ID for the client and add client 
                 information to the database on server side.
 server->server, synchronize the database between servers.
 
Client communicate:
  client sends P2P message: through the server it connects. The server parses the message and forward the message 
                            based on its "routing table" to the destination server. 
  client sends message through channel: 
